Package: securer
Title: Secure R Code Execution with Tool-Call IPC
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ian", "Flores Siaca", email = "iflores.siaca@hey.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Description: Provides sandboxed execution of R code with a bidirectional
    tool-call protocol over Unix domain sockets. Wraps a 'callr' session
    inside an OS-level sandbox (Seatbelt on macOS, bubblewrap on Linux,
    environment isolation on Windows) so that Large Language Model (LLM)
    generated code can compute results and call host-side tools without
    accessing the filesystem, network, or credentials.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://ian-flores.github.io/securer/,
    https://github.com/ian-flores/securer
BugReports: https://github.com/ian-flores/securer/issues
SystemRequirements: bubblewrap (bwrap, Linux, optional), sandbox-exec
    (macOS, included with OS, optional), PowerShell (Windows, included with
    OS, optional)
Language: en-US
Encoding: UTF-8
